channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: As Cohen Wobbles, Does the Case Against Trump Fall Down? (Trump Trial - Day 18)
Kamala Harris accepts invitation to debate Trump VP pick
item.description: President Biden's campaign announced this week that Vice President Kamala Harris will debate former President Donald Trump's eventual running mate in a televised CBS event.

item.title: Sen. Cotton Backs Rep. Rogers for Michigan's Open Senate Seat
item.description: In a move that could reshape Michigan's political landscape, Sen. Tom Cotton, R-Ark., has thrown his weight behind former Rep. Mike Rogers for the upcoming U.S. Senate race, intensifying an already heated battleground, the Daily Caller reported.

item.title: Harrison Butker's Official NFL Jersey Makes the Bestseller List As Wokesters Cry in Their Milk
Thomas Massie introduces bills to audit, abolish the Federal Reserve
item.description: Legislation has been introduced by Rep. Thomas Massie, R-Ky., has that seeks to end the Federal Reserve central banking system which has been in operation since 1913.

item.title: Rep. Jordan to Newsmax: Contempt Vote on AG Garland Necessary
item.description: Rep. Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, told Newsmax on Thursday the House Judiciary Committee which he chairs had no choice but to vote to hold Attorney General Merrick Garland in contempt of court.

item.title: In Sharp Rebuke of Biden, 16 House Dems Join GOP to Pass Bill to Force Weapons Shipments to Israel
'Red-hot momentum': GOP committee unleashes effort to win back White House with 'game-changing' tool
item.description: The Republican National Committee launched VotePro, a new tool to help Republicans communicate with voters as the party seeks to elect more candidates up and down the ballot in 2024.

item.title: Steve Forbes to Newsmax: Biden's Debate Strategy a 'Hail Mary'
item.description: Steve Forbes, chair and editor-in-chief of Forbes Media, expressed his views on the upcoming presidential debates and the current administration's performance during an interview with Newsmax on Thursday.

item.title: 'Drag Them': Missouri AG Minces No Words, Vows Action After Kansas City Tweet About Harrison Butker
How artificial intelligence is reshaping modern warfare
item.description: Harnessing AI is key to the United States staying ahead of adversaries in a competitive battlefield. Software companies are showing off their latest AI tools to military officials.

item.title: Franklin Graham to Newsmax: Fitting Father's Statue Has Him Holding Open Bible
item.description: A statue immortalizing the late Rev. Billy Graham was unveiled at the U.S. Capitol on Thursday by House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., with members of Graham's family, including his son Franklin Graham, in attendance.

Showdown: The blue states Trump aims to turn red in November
item.description: Former President Trump heads to Minnesota on Friday, to headline a state GOP fundraiser, as he aims to flip the blue state red in November's election and expand the map in his 2024 rematch with Biden

item.title: NY Times: Justice Alito's Home Flew US Flag Upside Down After Jan. 6
item.description: An American flag was photographed hanging upside down at the Virginia home of Supreme Court Justice Samuel Alito in January 2021, weeks after the Jan. 6 protests, The New York Times reported Thursday.
